<HEAD>Security Forces Find Huge Arsenal Of Terrorist Weapons</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELFAST, Northern Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Security forces found a large arsenal of weapons, including a Soviet-made rocket launcher, hidden in underground bunkers, police said today. The Royal Ulster Constabulary said `` a number of people'' were arrested for questioning about the caches, discovered on Monday and today around <LOCATION> Strabane </LOCATION>, <PERSON> County </PERSON> <PERSON> Tyrone </PERSON>, near <LOCATION> Northern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION>'s northwest border with the <LOCATION> Irish </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Republic </LOCATION> `` Security forces have found a huge arsenal of terrorist weapons,'' a police statement said. The haul included a Soviet RPG-7 rocket launcher and two warheads, more than 1,000 pounds of homemade explosives, two Soviet-made AKM assault rifles, one shotgun, a large quantity of ammunition and detonators, explosive fuses and propellant charges, police said. The arms were concealed in 40-gallon drums that had been welded together and buried in elaborately constructed bunkers under a hillside, police said. `` It is obvious that people within our community were fully aware of the presence of these caches,'' said a police spokesman, who requested anonymity. `` Where human life is being taken so frequently it is long past time that those who are aware of such activity should act more responsibly.'' The spokesman urged citizens to report any information about terrorist activities or arms so that `` lives can be saved.'' Last week, Sir <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Hermon </PERSON>, head of the <ORGANIZATION> Royal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ulster </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Constabulary </ORGANIZATION>, said the outlawed <ORGANIZATION> Irish </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> `` has very considerable quantities of very powerful weaponry which they have not yet used,'' including surface-to-air missiles. <LOCATION> Libya </LOCATION> is believed to have supplied the weapons to the <ORGANIZ