reaty in place we will have a <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> to <ORGANIZATION> Justice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> relationship that will be almost strictly law enforcement oriented,'' <PERSON> Kerry </PERSON> said. `` There will be an opportunity for creative requests that will let us see if there is cooperation.'' The Mutual Legal Assistance treaties are designed to provide a framework by which the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> can request the cooperation of the countries involved to obtain evidence to use in criminal prosecutions in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. Each of the six countries could make similar requests of the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>.
