different time periods that gave <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> a bigger portion of a smaller audience. Each rating point equals 904,000 households with televisions. The share is a percentage of sets in use. The week ending Sept. 25 was the first of the official new television season. However, <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> are maintaining the season does n't really begin until late October, when all three networks have premiered most of their new fall shows. <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> and CBS are airing reruns and movies to counter <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s two weeks of Olympics programming. <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s Thursday night coverage was the top-rated show of the week, followed by Saturday, Friday, Sunday, Wednesday, Tuesday and Monday. <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> followed with its rerun TV movie `` A Stranger Waits,'' and <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> made the top 10 with Tuesday night comedies, `` Head of the Class'' and `` Growing Pains.'' The lowest-rated shows of the week were: `` Cadets,'' `` Live! <PERSON> Dick </PERSON> <PERSON> Clark </PERSON> Presents,'' `` The Best of SCTV,'' `` 48 Hours,'' `` Beauty & amp; the <LOCATION> Beast </LOCATION>,'' `` <PERSON> Garry </PERSON> <PERSON> Shandling </PERSON> Alone in <LOCATION> Las </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Vegas </LOCATION>,'' `` Bodywatching,'' `` West 57th,'' `` First Impressions'' and `` <PERSON> Frank </PERSON>'s Place.''
