<HEAD>VP Debate, Playoff Starting Times Adjusted to Avoid Conflict</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The Oct. 5 starting times for the vice-presidential debate and the major league baseball playoffs have been juggled to avoid a conflict, officials involved said Tuesday. The 90-minute debate between Democrat <PERSON> Lloyd </PERSON> <PERSON> Bentsen </PERSON> and Republican <PERSON> Dan </PERSON> <PERSON> Quayle </PERSON> was moved from a 9 p.m. EDT starting time to 8:30 p.m. The start of the first game of the American League playoffs, scheduled for the home of the East Division winner, was moved from 8:28 p.m. to 1:20 p.m., and the first pitch of game two in the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> League </ORGANIZATION> playoffs at <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> was pushed back from 3:07 p.m. to 10:08 p.m. <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> will televise the baseball games. All the major networks will televise the debate.
