<BYLINE>By RICHARD PYLE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MANAMA, Bahrain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The first U.S.-flagged Kuwaiti tanker to sail without a close escort of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> warships left <LOCATION> Kuwait </LOCATION> Tuesday, heading south through waters where three mines have been discovered in the past five days. Although traveling alone, the 81,283-ton oil products carrier <LOCATION> Surf </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> would not be unprotected should trouble arise, <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> military sources said. `` She's on her way, and will be under surveillance at all times,'' said one source, insisting on anonymity. Attacks on commercial shipping stopped Aug. 20 when <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION> declared a cease-fire in their 8-year-old war. However, fears of mines were heightened with reports that Italian mine-hunters found an explosive device floating in the south-central <LOCATION> Persian </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION> _ the third such discovery in five days and the fifth since Aug. 19. <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> is considered responsible for virtually all gulf mines. <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>'s navy commander said Tuesday that <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>'s territorial waters in the <LOCATION> northern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> gulf </LOCATION> are cleared of mines, as are major parts of the international waters, the official <LOCATION> Islamic </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Republic </LOCATION> news agency reported in a dispatch monitored in <LOCATION> Nicosia </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Cyprus </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> IRNA </ORGANIZATION> quoted Rear Adm. <PERSON> Mohammed-Hussein </PERSON> <PERSON> Malekzadegan </PERSON> as saying an Iranian warship and two guided missile boats arrived in the northern gulf ports of Imam <PERSON> Khomeini </PERSON> and <PERSON> Mahshahr </PERSON> after clearing the shipping channels in <LOCATION> Khur </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Musa </LOCATION> of mines. <PERSON> Khur </PERSON> <PERSON> Musa </PERSON> is the extended bay leading to the two ports. <LOCAT