was withdrawn earlier this month and was not replaced. The <ORGANIZATION> Pentagon </ORGANIZATION> also has curtailed air patrols and other escort activities. That cost had been estimated by <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> officials at $ 20 million a month. Nine Americans were killed in helicopter and jet crashes during the operation. Other incidents included the mining of the supertanker <LOCATION> Bridgeton </LOCATION> in the first convoy July 24, 1987, an Iranian Silkworm missile attack that disabled the tanker <LOCATION> Sea </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Isle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> at <LOCATION> Kuwait </LOCATION>, and the near-sinking of the frigate USS <PERSON> Samuel </PERSON> <PERSON> B. </PERSON> <PERSON> Roberts </PERSON> by a mine April 14. The <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> forces retaliated, wrecking two oil platforms and sinking or damaging six Iranian naval craft in an attack April 18. On July 3, the <LOCATION> Vincennes </LOCATION> mistook an Iranian jetliner for an attacking military jet and shot it down, killing all 290 aboard.
