 <ORGANIZATION> Kroger </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> says it would sell stores and food processing plants and reduce its work force as part of a $ 4.6 billion restructuring aimed at defeating two takeover bids. <ORGANIZATION> Kroger </ORGANIZATION> officials contended Monday that the restructuring would be more lucrative for shareholders than a $ 4.6 billion offer by <ORGANIZATION> Kohlberg </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kravis </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Roberts </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> or a competing $ 4.32 billion offer from <ORGANIZATION> Dart </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp </ORGANIZATION>. Spokesmen for <PERSON> Dart </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> Kohlberg </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kravis </ORGANIZATION> declined comment Monday.
