/PERSON> said <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> dealers work out the final post-lease purchase price with the customer. Included in the <ORGANIZATION> GMAC </ORGANIZATION> promotion, which runs through Dec. 31, are the <ORGANIZATION> Chevrolet </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corsica </ORGANIZATION> and Beretta, the Pontiac Grand Am, three Cutlass models and two GMC truck lines, company spokesman <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Andrews </PERSON> said. `` What we've done is a corporate-wide program,'' <PERSON> Andrews </PERSON> said. `` Leasing programs have been done by each of the divisions. Under our old programs, the purchase price was determined at the end of lease and was the fair market value of the car.'' Knowing the post-lease or residual value of the car up front is an advantage to the buyer in considering whether to buy out the lease at its end, <PERSON> Andrews </PERSON> said. The end of auto interest deductions on federal tax returns has made leasing a more attractive option, especially for young families trying to meet mortgage payments, which still are partly tax deductible, he said. `` It's also a lifestyle thing,'' <PERSON> Andrews </PERSON> said. `` It is n't important for people to own things like it used to be. National promotion of the SmartLease program began during Sunday night's telecast of the Summer Olympics. Extensive electronic and print ads are planned.
