k </PERSON> raised a potential conflict involving <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION>'s role in the acquisiton of a <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> retail clothing chain, Palais Royal of <LOCATION> Houston </LOCATION>, and the company's chairman, <PERSON> Moselle </PERSON> <PERSON> Pollack </PERSON>, who is the judge's wife The newspaper said <PERSON> Palais </PERSON> <PERSON> Royal </PERSON> was founded by Mrs. <PERSON> Pollack </PERSON>'s family, the Erlichs, 60 years ago and was close to being acquried by an unidentified company If the deal is completed, Mrs. <PERSON> Pollack </PERSON> and her husband stand to receive about $ 9 million, the <ORGANIZATION> Times </ORGANIZATION> quoted sources as saying. <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION>'s attorneys want <PERSON> Pollack </PERSON> removed from the case because they feel he might appear to be biased in favor of <ORGANIZATION> Drexel </ORGANIZATION>, which is involved in raising financing for the deal, the newspaper said.
